    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices of various designs, often a slender bar-like object, used in weaving or netting. In weaving, it passes the thread or yarn of the weft to and from one edge of the cloth to the other between the threads or yarns of the warp.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
